  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get free website?",
  "response": "Creating a free website is easier than ever thanks to various platforms that offer free website building services. Here's a step-by-step guide on how you can get a free website:\n\n### 1. **Choose a Website Builder**\nSeveral platforms offer free website creation services. Some popular options include:\n- **WordPress.com** - Great for blogs and simple websites.\n- **Wix** - User-friendly with a drag-and-drop interface.\n- **Weebly** - Offers a variety of themes and built-in features.\n- **Google Sites** - Simple and integrates well with other Google services.\n- **GitHub Pages** - Best for developers looking to showcase projects.\n\n### 2. **Sign Up**\nCreate an account on the chosen platform. You may need to provide an email address and some other basic information.\n\n### 3. **Select a Template or Theme**\nMost website builders offer a selection of templates or themes to get you started. Pick one that suits your content and aesthetic preferences.\n\n### 4. **Customize Your Website**\nUse the platform's tools to add your own content, images, and other elements. Customize the design to match your branding.\n\n### 5. **Add Essential Pages**\nMost websites will need at least the following pages:\n- **Homepage** - The main landing page.\n- **About** - Information about you or your business.\n- **Contact** - Ways for visitors to get in touch.\n- **Blog/News** - If you plan on regularly updating with new posts or articles.\n- **Services/Products** - For showcasing what you offer.\n\n### 6. **Publish**\nOnce you're satisfied with your website, use the platform's publish feature to make it live. Most free website builders automatically assign you a free subdomain (e.g., yoursite.wordpress.com).\n\n### 7. **Promote Your Website**\nShare the link to your website on social media, email signatures, business cards, and any other relevant platforms to start getting visitors.\n\n### Additional Tips\n- **SEO Optimization:** Make sure your site is search engine friendly by using proper tags, descriptions, and keywords.\n- **Responsive Design:** Ensure that your website looks good on both desktop and mobile devices.\n- **Analytics:** If possible, set up Google Analytics or use the built-in analytics tools to track your site's performance.\n\n### Considerations\n- **Free Domain**: You'll typically get a subdomain from the website builder (e.g., yoursite.wix.com). If you need a custom domain, you'll likely need to upgrade to a paid plan.\n- **Ads:** Some free website builders might display ads on your site.\n- **Storage/Bandwidth Limits:** Free plans usually have limitations on storage and bandwidth.\n\nBy following these steps, you'll have a free website up and running in no time!",
